<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFE7FFDCFCD62D75F2BDFB33" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFE7FFDCFCD62D75F2BDFB33" blockId="16.[828,1437,619,2083]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE7FFDCFCD62D75F2A1FD53" bold="true" box="[828,944,619,643]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae reddish (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFB6D2D72F5CDFD53" box="[1159,1244,620,643]" captionStart="Figs 3" captionStartId="4.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[242,1332,205,1992]" captionTargetId="figure-13@4.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 3A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys favachae sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177533" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177533/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Antennomere II longer than III. Pronotum with smoky stripe reaching posterior margin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFBB52DD2F5A3FD33" box="[1119,1202,716,739]" captionStart="Figs 3" captionStartId="4.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[242,1332,205,1992]" captionTargetId="figure-13@4.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 3A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys favachae sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177533" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177533/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth and almost whole third rostral segment (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFBF12C12F566FCF3" box="[1051,1143,780,803]" captionStart="Figs 14" captionStartId="18.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[180,1414,203,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 14A–E. Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig. 14E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE7FFDCFB6D2C15F436FCF3" bold="true" box="[1159,1319,779,803]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFCA92C32F2DFFC93" box="[835,974,812,835]" captionStart="Figs 14" captionStartId="18.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[180,1414,203,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 14A–E. Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Figs 14A–D</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles developed, bent inwards, acuminate (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFBED2C52F577FCB3" box="[1031,1126,844,867]" captionStart="Figs 14" captionStartId="18.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[180,1414,203,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 14A–E. Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig 14A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup elongated, parallel to dorsal rim, and slightly concave; inner (proximal) part truncate and strongly curved, ventral angle with dentiform process; outer (distal) part tonguelike (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFC922CD2F2EEFC33" box="[888,1023,972,995]" captionStart="Figs 14" captionStartId="18.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[180,1414,203,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 14A–E. Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Figs 14C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; anterior lobe square, large, and directed to dorsal rim; lateral lobe rounded and large (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFBE82B12F56CFBF3" box="[1026,1149,1036,1059]" captionStart="Figs 14" captionStartId="18.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[180,1414,203,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 14A–E. Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Figs 14C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dense short setae on lateral excavation; posterior face triangular (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFA872B32F297FBB3" captionStart="Figs 14" captionStartId="18.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[180,1414,203,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 14A–E. Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Figs 14C,D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions acuminate, narrow, apices curved inwards, ventrolateral side furrowed, dorsal side with brown spot; level or just surpassing posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE7FFDCFB832BB2F5DBFB13" box="[1129,1226,1196,1219]" captionStart="Figs 14" captionStartId="18.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[180,1414,203,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-13@18.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs 14A–E. Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177553/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE7FFDCFB362BB5F48DFB13" bold="true" box="[1244,1436,1195,1219]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFE7FFDCFCB02BF2F55AFA53" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" type="description">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFE7FFDCFCB02BF2F55AFA53" blockId="16.[828,1437,619,2083]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE7FFDCFCB02BF2F2EAFAD3" bold="true" box="[858,1019,1260,1283]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Measurements</emphasis>
(n = 1). Total length 16.3; head length 1.4; head width 3.3; pronotum width 10.9; abdomen width 8.9; length of antennomeres: I – 0.7; II – 1.9; III – 1.5; IV – 5.7; V: missing; scutellum length 8.0; scutellum width 6.3; pronotum length 3.0.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFE7FFDCFCD62A95F481F873" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFE7FFDCFCD62A95F481F873" blockId="16.[828,1437,619,2083]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE7FFDCFCD62A95F53DFA73" bold="true" box="[828,1068,1419,1443]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFE7FFDCFB5A2A92F468FA73" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1200,1401,1420,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalinofasciatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE7FFDCFB5A2A92F468FA73" box="[1200,1401,1420,1443]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">H. hyalinofasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFE7FFDCFA942A92F278FA13" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares with 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFE7FFDCFC0D2AB2F571FA13" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[999,1120,1452,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE7FFDCFC0D2AB2F571FA13" box="[999,1120,1452,1475]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">H. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFE7FFDCFB8F2AB2F5A4FA13" box="[1125,1205,1452,1475]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the ventral rim expansions directed inwards. The species 
